                type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> and
                    Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> visited
                    Washington June 25 to 29, 1954 for talks with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> and Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> on a wide range of matters of
                    mutual interest, including <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>. Extensive
                    documentation on the <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1"
                        >Churchill</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> visit
                    to Washington in June 1954 is presented in <ref target="frus1952-54v06p1">volume
                        VI</ref>.</p>
            </div>
